    <Folder>
      <name>Intelligence Summary</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>AI Council Assessment</name>
        <styleUrl>#intel</styleUrl>
        <description>The synthesized intelligence assessment reveals a globally dispersed U.S. military posture with concentrated activities in the Mediterranean, European, and Indo-Pacific theaters. High-altitude ISR platforms such as the RC-135 Rivet Joint and Dassault Falcon 900 are actively conducting electronic intelligence gathering in the Eastern Mediterranean, likely in response to regional tensions involving Iran and NATO operations. The deployment of the USS George Washington (CVN-73) to the Philippine Sea underscores sustained U.S. naval presence in the Western Pacific, supporting regional allies amid South China Sea tensions. Concurrently, NATO efforts to counter Russian maritime shadow fleet operations are evident with the UK seizure of a Russian shadow tanker in the English Channel. Domestically, the USS Harry S. Truman (CVN-75) remains in port for major overhaul, indicating a temporary reduction in Atlantic carrier availability. The data reflects a strategic emphasis on ISR, maritime security, and readiness amid escalating regional conflicts and great power competition. Training activities remain robust, particularly in European airspace, with multiple platforms conducting pilot training sorties. The overall assessment indicates a U.S. military posture that is both proactive and adaptive, balancing deterrence operations with readiness exercises across multiple theaters.</description>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>0,0,0</coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
